
{center}
{subhead} How to connect to Currant Bun ISP{def}{p}
Article by Alan Bailey
{left}
{p} {p}

Let's Begin:
{p} {p}
1) Start MiamiInit, now select continue then select (Analogue/ISDN Modem)
and click continue, now select the serial port (i use the built in port)
then click continue, now select the serial device (i use the miami driver)
then click continue, now select your modem and change the dial prefix to
ATDT and click continue miami will now test your modem, if all goe's well
you'll get to enter a phone number which is "{bold}0845-6621432{nobold}" enter this and
click continue, now enter your login name as "signup" and your password as
"guest", make sure the ip adress is dynamic and protocol is PPP, click
continue, you now have the dialler screen click dial and miami will go
online and grab some information from the isp, once offline you get to enter
your real name, do this and deselect the print option and click continue.
{p} {p}
2) Start Miami, and from the settings menu select "Import from MiamiInit V3"
now go to the dialler option on the left side of miami and in the login id
put "signup" and in the password put "guest" now save your settingsand go 
online and start your browser (i used voyager) you now have to go to the
signup page which is "{link http://www.currantbun.com/setup/signup.htm}http://www.currantbun.com/setup/signup.htm{end}" fill in
details and submit your form if/when successfull you will be given your
user name and password, write these down, you'll have to download something
now so start the download and then abort as you do not need this file and go
offline now edit your Miamisettings again but in the dialler options put in
your new login id and your password and save again.
{p} {p}
That's it you now have an account with currant bun.
{p} {p}
3) Start YAM, from the settings menu select configuration and in first steps
put your name and e-mail address then put the pop3 server which is
"{bold}pop3.currantbun.com{nobold}" and your password you were given after you setup the
account then select TCP/IP now enter smtp as "{bold}smtp.currantbun.com{nobold}" now
click on new in the receice mail section and enter "{bold}pop3.currantbun.com{nobold}"
and your user id and password and save your settings, you should now be able
to send and receive mail.
{p} {p}
That all folks.
{p} {p}
